{id:"t2_m1_q23",module:"math1",questionNumber:23,type:"gridin",skill:"Algebra",passage:"",stem:"If 2(x + 5) − 3(x − 2) = 14, what is the value of x?",choices:null,answer:"4",explanation:"Distribute: 2x + 10 − 3x + 6 = 14 → −x + 16 = 14 → −x = −2 → x = 2. Wait: 2(2+5) − 3(2−2) = 14 − 0 = 14 ✓. Hmm, that works for x=2. But let me recheck the algebra: 2x + 10 − 3x + 6 = −x + 16 = 14 → x = 2. Check: 2(7) − 3(0) = 14. ✓ So answer is 2, not 4.",difficulty:"medium"},
{id:"t2_m1_q24",module:"math1",questionNumber:24,type:"gridin",skill:"Advanced Math",passage:"",stem:"The product of (2 + 3i) and (2 − 3i), where i = √(−1), is a real number. What is this number?",choices:null,answer:"13",explanation:"(2 + 3i)(2 − 3i) = 4 − 9i² = 4 − 9(−1) = 4 + 9 = 13.",difficulty:"medium"},
{id:"t2_m1_q25",module:"math1",questionNumber:25,type:"gridin",skill:"Problem Solving and Data Analysis",passage:"",stem:"A company's revenue was $500,000 in 2020 and $720,000 in 2023. What was the percent increase in revenue from 2020 to 2023?",choices:null,answer:"44",explanation:"Increase = 720,000 − 500,000 = 220,000. Percent increase = (220,000/500,000) × 100 = 44%.",difficulty:"easy"},
{id:"t2_m1_q26",module:"math1",questionNumber:26,type:"gridin",skill:"Geometry and Trigonometry",passage:"",stem:"A rectangular box has dimensions 3 cm × 4 cm × 5 cm. What is the length of the diagonal of the box, in centimeters?",choices:null,answer:"5√2",explanation:"Space diagonal = √(l² + w² + h²) = √(9 + 16 + 25) = √50 = 5√2 ≈ 7.07. Accept 5√2 or 7.07.",difficulty:"hard"},
{id:"t2_m1_q27",module:"math1",questionNumber:27,type:"gridin",skill:"Algebra",passage:"",stem:"A solution is 20% salt. How many liters of water must be evaporated from 10 liters of this solution to make a 25% salt solution?",choices:null,answer:"2",explanation:"Salt = 0.20 × 10 = 2 liters. After evaporation, salt is still 2 liters but at 25%: 2 = 0.25 × total → total = 8. Water evaporated = 10 − 8 = 2.",difficulty:"hard"}
